claim.claim-text:
1. A system enabled to provide contactless payment comprising:
an electronic device including an authentication function enabling restriction of use of said electronic device;
a contactless payment circuit operable to communicate with said electronic device;
a first reader in communication with said contactless payment circuit, said first reader operably coupled to said electronic device;
a second reader for receiving user account information from said contactless payment circuit; and
a transaction processing system for receiving user account information from said second reader and authorizing payment based on said user account information,
wherein payment functionality of said contactless payment circuit is enabled for use or disabled based on a restriction status of said electronic device via said first reader, said restriction status corresponding to whether said use of said electronic device has been restricted via said authentication function.

2. A method for authenticating contactless payment, comprising:
bringing a contactless payment circuit in proximity to a reader, said contactless payment circuit being operably coupled to a smart card reader;
detecting an attempted activation of said contactless payment circuit;
determining an authorized use status of an electronic device, said electronic device operably coupled to said smart card reader to which said contactless payment circuit is in communication; and
enabling said contactless payment circuit to provide data to said reader based on said authorized use status of said device via said smart card reader.
